      "content": "Tariffs are a double-edged sword that often hurt consumers more than they help domestic industries in the long run. While they can temporarily shield local businesses from foreign competition, the resulting higher prices for imported goods are ultimately paid by American shoppers. Furthermore, these measures frequently trigger retaliatory tariffs from trading partners, which can damage U.S. exporters and disrupt global supply chains. Ultimately, the economic data suggests that free trade policies tend to generate more overall wealth and lower prices for everyone involved.",
